npx is needed to create the project

npx create-react-app <project name>

npm install create-react-app -g

function calculator(a,b,c) {
var operator = {
    add:  a+b,
    minus: a-b
  };
return operator[c];
}

switch(true) {
	case 'Yellow': return "yellow";
}

/// state and life cycle

Mounting

[Initial state or default props]
componentWillMount -> render -> componentDidMount

Updating

shouldComponent update -> true -> componentWillUpdate -> render -> componentDidUpdate
shouldComponent update -> false -> stop

Unmounting

componentWillUnmount

everything in render (react) must have a wrapper. (1 div);

react-router-dom


<BrowserRouter>
<div>
 <Switch>
  <Route path="/about" component={About} />
  <Route path="/login" component={Login} />
  <Route exact path="/" component={Properties} />
  </Switch>
</BrowserRouter>


